Rating: 4
This recipe makes a monsterous six portions. I wonder if they really mean 3-1/2 pounds of potatoes?? I used a 3 oz. package of cream cheese, about 2/3 cups of sour cream, and 1/2 stick of margarine (as a previous reviewer suggested using less cream cheese and using 1/2 stick of butter). Deleted any salt; used about 1/4 tsp. of white pepper and a generous sprinkle of garlic powder. I also increased the milk to about a cup. (I probably needed more liquid as no food store in this town sells fresh chives, so I used about 1+1/2 Tbs. of dried instead.) Do make this recipe, as it is DELICIOUS!!! A hint for those of you who cook for 2 (as I do): When it comes time to bake the gratin, butter 3 8-1/2 x 4-1/2 inch glass loaf pans, divide the potatoes evenly between the 3, and you will have potatoes for the night you make it and two leftover meals that you can either refrigerate or freeze.

